# Study Planner System

The Study Planner is the execution engine of learning discipline.

It turns goals into daily action.

---

# Product Vision

The Study Planner must:

- convert goals into structured schedules
- optimize study time allocation
- adapt to user performance
- reduce procrastination
- align with exam deadlines

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

StudyPlannerController (Riverpod)

↓

StudyPlannerState

↓

StudyPlannerRepository

↓

AI Scheduling Engine

---

# State Management

StudyPlannerState includes:

- loading
- generated
- updated
- syncing
- error

Core Data:

- weeklyPlan
- dailyPlan
- studySessions
- examCountdown
- workloadBalance
- AIRecommendations

---

# Planning Logic

AI generates plans based on:

- exam date
- available hours per day
- weak topics
- course progress
- user consistency

---

# Plan Types

- Daily Plan
- Weekly Plan
- Revision Plan
- Exam Countdown Plan

---

# AI Scheduling Rules

AI must:

- avoid overload
- prioritize weak topics
- distribute revision cycles
- include rest periods
- adjust dynamically

---

# Navigation Rules

Study Planner connects to:

- Courses
- Flashcards
- Quiz Engine
- Mock Exams

---

# Offline Behaviour

- view-only offline mode
- no AI recalculation offline
- cached plans remain accessible

---

# API Contracts

GET /planner

POST /planner/generate

POST /planner/update

GET /planner/status

---

# Analytics Events

planner_generate

planner_view

planner_session_started

planner_session_completed

planner_adjusted

---

# UI Composition Rules

Study Planner must include:

- calendar view
- daily task list
- progress indicators
- AI suggestion panel
- exam countdown widget

---

# UX Rules

- reduce overwhelm
- focus on 3–5 tasks per day
- highlight priority tasks
- show time estimates

---

# Error Handling

- fallback to cached plan
- allow manual override
- retry AI generation safely

---

# Performance

- plan generation <2s target
- UI load <200ms

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- calendar accessibility navigation
- readable task structure
- screen reader compatibility

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Scheduling engine

Task prioritization logic

State updates

Widget Tests:

Calendar UI

Daily plan UI

AI suggestions panel

Integration Tests:

Full plan generation flow

Plan adjustment flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating study planner features:

- always use AI-driven scheduling
- always prioritize weak topics
- always enforce workload balance
- never overload daily plans